Description.LocalizedString: An iconoclastic, bold dress designed by her own hand.
A blood-soaked, edgy dress she designed and crafted herself.
A tormented artist carrying the guilt for the loss of her brother rises from despair to create surrealist, absurd art.
Her art displayed her reality, an absurd consciousness marred with blood and darkness.
The absurd edges of reality forged a sharp blade out of the palette knife she once used to paint her murals.
The absurd edges of reality forged a blood dripping blade out of the palette knife she once used to paint her murals.
A gifted code breaker working for the CIA, Jonah was haunted by a sequence that he could not decipher: 8, 25, 19, 44, 1; -20.37, -69.85; 13, 2, 26, 11, 1.
He was tormented by the staggering number of civilian casualties caused by the Kwantana operation.
Pair of casual shorts to blend in with civilians during his coffee breaks.
Pair of shorts marred with blood.
A relaxed, clean shirt for mulling over complex equations from history's leading mathematicians.
A wine colored shirt for style and comfort.
A blood-soaked shirt that showed the damage done.
